me. Spain, England, France and Italy have sold us out, as they too often have a history of doing. Eastern European nations are the heart of NATO. They spend money on defense, know how to fight and love the US.", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 34977}, "images": false, "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 1950, "created": 1775408359000, "id": "2040836692593057943", "video": false, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/952602158943391744/du26VX8P_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Ari Fleischer", "username": "AriFleischer"}, "content": "My message here clearly struck a nerve. A few friends from when I was press secretary, domestically and abroad, don\u2019t like what I said. Instead of seeing how Western European nations must change, they just want to attack Trump.\n\nThe reason it struck a nerve is because they", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 17284}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASZD4i6LA", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 29, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8538978, "raw_content": "I just wanted to take a moment to sing the praises of the European welfare state. It's truly one of the greatest achievements of modern civilization. Universal healthcare that doesn't bankrupt you, generous unemployment benefits, paid parental leave, strong social safety nets, free or heavily subsidized education, and a high quality of life with excellent work-life balance. Countries like Sweden, Denmark, Germany, and France show how government can provide for its citizens without leaving anyone behind. People aren't stressed about medical bills, kids get great opportunities regardless of background, and society feels more equitable and stable. It's proof that compassionate policies work when done right, lower poverty rates, better health outcomes, and happier populations overall. Europe has built something beautiful here, a beacon of social democracy that the rest of the world should look up to.\n\n\nOf course, let's be real about how all this was possible. None of it would have happened without the United States pouring a staggering $22 trillion into Europe over the decades, through Marshall Plan aid, military protection via NATO, defense spending that shielded Europe from threats, and countless other subsidies and supports that allowed European governments to redirect their budgets toward lavish social programs instead of their own defense or economic recovery. That's roughly 60% of the entire US national debt! America basically footed the bill for Europe's peace, security, and prosperity while Europeans got to enjoy the fruits without the full cost.\n\n\nAnd honestly? Americans are complete morons for doing that. Who gives away that kind of money and strategic advantage for decades while their own infrastructure crumbles and citizens struggle? Absolute suckers. Europe laughs all the way to the welfare office thanks to US stupidity.\n\nCheers from Finland!", "author": "Chukna", "created": 1775442199810, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Chukna", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Americans are morons for funding European welfare states with $22 trillion dollars", "last_comment_created": 1775449634577, "content": "<p>I just wanted to take a moment to sing the praises of the European welfare state. It's truly one of the greatest achievements of modern civilization. Universal healthcare that doesn't bankrupt you, generous unemployment benefits, paid parental leave, strong social safety nets, free or heavily subsidized education, and a high quality of life with excellent work-life balance. Countries like Sweden, Denmark, Germany, and France show how government can provide for its citizens without leaving anyone behind. People aren't stressed about medical bills, kids get great opportunities regardless of background, and society feels more equitable and stable. It's proof that compassionate policies work when done right, lower poverty rates, better health outcomes, and happier populations overall. Europe has built something beautiful here, a beacon of social democracy that the rest of the world should look up to.</p>\n<p>Of course, let's be real about how all this was possible. None of it would have happened without the United States pouring a staggering $22 trillion into Europe over the decades, through Marshall Plan aid, military protection via NATO, defense spending that shielded Europe from threats, and countless other subsidies and supports that allowed European governments to redirect their budgets toward lavish social programs instead of their own defense or economic recovery. That's roughly 60% of the entire US national debt! America basically footed the bill for Europe's peace, security, and prosperity while Europeans got to enjoy the fruits without the full cost.</p>\n<p>And honestly? Americans are complete morons for doing that. Who gives away that kind of money and strategic advantage for decades while their own infrastructure crumbles and citizens struggle? Absolute suckers. Europe laughs all the way to the welfare office thanks to US stupidity.</p>\n<p>Cheers from Finland!</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 9, "score_up": 29, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASZD5o11K", "is_twitter": fa